description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity exists for a Senior Mental Health Support Worker to work within the Mental Health &amp; Learning Disabilities Liaison Team based at South Block, St Mary’s Hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic self-motivated applicant who enjoys working in a fast paced team. The team work across St Mary’s with a person centered approach which includes providing support for people with Dementia, Crisis assessments in the Emergency Department and supporting ward areas to provide reasonable adjustments for people with Learning Disabilities. We aim to improve the parity of care for people with mental health and learning disabilities in the acute hospital and work with their family and carers to ensure they have the best possible care and treatment. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This position is suitable for a highly motivated team player who is able to work under pressure. This team will be moving to a 24/7 coverage in the coming months so rotation of shifts will be an expectation of the role. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;At present the funding for these posts is until the end of March 2021 but it is highly likely that this will be extended into permanent positions due to the MH&amp;LD Division wide transformation programme currently taking place. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a developing service we are looking for applicants who are passionate about improving the experience for people who access support and treatment and St Mary’s and we welcome any ideas to develop and improve the service we provide. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should have excellent written and verbal communication skills and be able to interact at all levels. Attention to detail and proven ability to work to tight deadlines are essential for this role, as well as a high level of accuracy, data management skills and proven IT skills particularly in Paris and E-Care Logic. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We offer a supportive working environment, we have a robust supervision policy insitu and there is access to training opportunities to assist you to realize your potential and achieve a greater degree of job satisfaction, as well as the usual NHS discounts, pension, salary and annual leave entitlement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We look forward to seeing your application. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
